# Cursor Rules for OPTA API Documentation MCP Server

## Code Language
- All source code must be written in English
- Comments, variable names, function names, and documentation should be in English
- Only user-facing messages and README can be in Spanish

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all source files
- Follow ESLint and Prettier standards
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add JSDoc comments for public functions and classes

## Project Structure
- Keep the existing directory structure
- Place new files in appropriate directories
- Use index.ts files for clean exports

## MCP Server Guidelines
- All MCP tool names should be descriptive and in English
- Error messages should be clear and informative
- Log messages should be in English for debugging purposes

## Documentation
- README.md can be in Spanish for user convenience
- Code comments and JSDoc should be in English
- API documentation should be in English 